(13440, 791, 'top_section_top_section_copy', 'Situated between the vast prairie that extends to the Rockies and the vibrant urban expanse of Denver, Aster Conservatory Green offers residents a Colorado experience that combines the best of the outdoors with decidedly urban options. In addition, the Conservatory Green neighborhood has a terrific mix of restaurants, shops and entertainment of its own. How you choose to mix the spectrum of options is up to you; it’s the beauty of living here.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The Shops at Northfield Stapleton for shopping and entertainment</li>\r\n 	<li>Conservatory Green Park &amp; Plaza with performance green, water feature, shade structure and gathering space.</li>\r\n 	<li>Rocky Mountain Arsenal National</li>\r\n 	<li>Wildlife Refuge and Dick’s Sporting Goods Park</li>\r\n 	<li>Miles of hiking and biking trails</li>\r\n 	<li>10 minutes to downtown Denver</li>\r\n 	<li>20 minutes to Denver International Airport</li>\r\n</ul>'),
